---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Amplifly was built by Lily Stone, a neurodivergent founder who wanted a tool that worked with her brain instead of against it."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 bg-deep-navy">
    <div class="container px-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-medium-blue text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">About Amplifly</p>
      <h1 class="text-white text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-6">
        Built from lived experience,<br/>
        <span class="text-bright-blue">not a feature brief.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-medium-blue text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Amplifly started as a personal tool. It became an app because nothing else was
        honest about what ND brains actually need.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container px-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-start">
        <img
          src="/images/lily.jpeg"
          alt="Lily Stone, founder of Amplifly"
          class="w-40 h-40 rounded-2xl object-cover flex-shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Hi, I'm Lily 👋</h2>
          <p class="text-bright-blue text-sm font-semibold mb-4">Founder of Amplifly</p>
          <p class="text-accessible-gray leading-relaxed mb-4">
            I'm a neurodivergent founder who spent years trying to use productivity tools
            that assumed my brain worked the same every day. It doesn't. None of ours do.
          </p>
          <p class="text-accessible-gray leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Amplifly grew out of a simple question: what if an app actually started with
            how your brain feels today, instead of treating every morning like a blank slate?
            The five brain states, the techniques, the operating manual — all of it came from
            trying to understand my own patterns and finding no tool that did it honestly.
          </p>
          <p class="text-accessible-gray leading-relaxed">
            The technology should adapt to neurodivergent minds, not the other way around.
            That's the whole point.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we actually built -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-soft-blue">
    <div class="container px-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-8">What Amplifly actually is</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        {[
          {
            title: 'A brain state tracker',
            desc: 'Five states — Sharp, Spicy, Flat, Foggy, Scattered — that capture how ND brains actually feel day to day. You pick one each morning. No wrong answer.',
          },
          {
            title: 'A condition recommender that learns',
            desc: 'Twelve evidence-informed techniques across four phases. An on-device Thompson-sampling bandit learns which conditions work for your specific brain state, time of day, and ND profile. Research priors from day one, personal data as you build history.',
          },
          {
            title: 'A flow logger',
            desc: 'After any deep work block, log how long, how locked-in you were, what helped, what drained you, and which condition you used. 60 seconds. This is the data that builds your manual.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Your operating manual',
            desc: 'The Manual tab synthesises everything into a living document: your sharpest hour, your highest-flow brain state, your top helpers and drains, your streaks, what the recommender has figured out. The more you log, the sharper it gets.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Fully offline, genuinely private',
            desc: 'Everything lives in your phone\'s local storage. No analytics, no crash reports, no third-party SDKs. A free optional account lets you sync across devices via Supabase — encrypted in transit, never sold or shared.',
          },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-deep-navy font-bold text-lg mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-accessible-gray leading-relaxed text-base">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-deep-navy">
    <div class="container px-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-white text-2xl font-bold mb-10">What guides us</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {[
          { icon: '🧠', title: 'ND brains, not \'fixed\' brains', desc: 'Amplifly doesn\'t treat neurodivergence as a problem to solve. It treats it as a context to understand.' },
          { icon: '🔒', title: 'Privacy as a feature', desc: 'Your data is yours. Everything on-device by default. Optional sync, fully explained. No surprises.' },
          { icon: '🤖', title: 'Honest technology', desc: 'The recommendation engine is a Thompson-sampling bandit, not "AI magic." The forecast is a neural network with documented architecture. We explain how things work.' },
          { icon: '📈', title: 'Progress over perfection', desc: 'Missed a day? Your streak resets but your posteriors don\'t. The app never punishes you for being human.' },
        ].map(v => (
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="text-2xl flex-shrink-0">{v.icon}</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">{v.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-medium-blue text-sm leading-relaxed">{v.desc}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container px-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Get in touch</h2>
      <p class="text-accessible-gray mb-6">Questions, feedback, or support — we read every email.</p>
      <a href="mailto:hello@amplifly.app"
         class="inline-block bg-deep-navy hover:bg-navy-light text-white font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-xl transition-colors">
        hello@amplifly.app
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
